I"ë<h3 class="index-h3">Thanks for using WoodpeckerÔºÅ</h3>

<p><strong>Woodpecker Supports both physical device and simulator iOS8.0+, Objective-C and Swift.</strong></p>

<p>To use Woodpecker, you need import a framework to your project, then it will start and connect to Woodpecker client automatically. If you are work with physical device, please ensure your app and Woodpecker are in the same network.<br /></p>

<p>If you‚Äôre developing a Mac app, please check <a href="/usagemac.html">Woodpecker for MacOS</a></p>

<p><strong>1. CocoaPods:</strong></p>

<div class="highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code>pod 'WoodPeckeriOS', :configurations =&gt; ['Debug']
</code></pre></div></div>
<p>Use <code class="highlighter-rouge">pod update WoodPeckeriOS</code> to update the latest version.
<br />
<br /></p>

<p><strong>2. Carthage:</strong></p>

<div class="highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code>binary "https://raw.githubusercontent.com/appwoodpecker/woodpecker-ios/master/WoodPeckeriOS-Carthage.json"
</code></pre></div></div>
<p><br /></p>

<p><strong>3. Manual Setup:</strong></p>

<ol>
  <li>Download <a href="/assets/framework/WoodPeckeriOS.framework.zip">WoodPeckeriOS.framework</a></li>
  <li>Import WoodPeckeriOS.framework to your project.</li>
  <li>If you like to use only in Debug configuration, please <a href="/manuallink.html">check this</a></li>
</ol>

<p><br /></p>

<p><strong>If you have the following problems:</strong></p>

<blockquote>
  <p><strong>Didn‚Äôt work with iOS 14 devices</strong></p>
</blockquote>

<p><br />
iOS 14 add a new permission for local network usage, please ensure your app has the permission, and if you build with the latest Xcode, please add these two items in Info.plist:</p>

<ol>
  <li>Add description in Privacy - Local Network Usage Description</li>
  <li>Add _adhp._tcp in Bonjour Service</li>
</ol>

<p><strong>In practice, you don‚Äôt need to remove these keys when build for AppStore, because the privacy alert won‚Äôt appear until we call any local network api, such as bonjour service or multicast</strong></p>

<p><img src="/assets/img/localnetwork.png" /></p>

<p><br /></p>
<blockquote>
  <p><strong>dyld: Library not loaded: @rpath/WoodPeckeriOS.framework/WoodPeckeriOS
Reason: image not found</strong></p>
</blockquote>

<p><br />
Please drag WoodPeckeriOS.framework to <code class="highlighter-rouge">Build Phases -&gt; Embed Framworks</code>.</p>

<p><img src="/assets/img/embedframework.png" />
<br /></p>
<blockquote>
  <p><strong>Mac client is always ‚Äúwaiting connect‚Äù</strong></p>
</blockquote>

<ol>
  <li>please ensure mac and app are in the same wifi.</li>
  <li>please ensure WoodPeckeriOS.framework was the latest version.</li>
  <li>connect to mac client manually, long press your iOS app‚Äôs screen with two fingers, you‚Äôll see the connection page, try search and connect to your mac client.</li>
  <li>If it still doesn‚Äôt work, <a href="/contact.html">click here</a>.</li>
</ol>

<p><br /></p>
<blockquote>
  <p><strong>I often connect to other‚Äôs mac.</strong></p>
</blockquote>

<p>You could make some options to specify which client you‚Äôd like to connect, <a href="/connection.html">see advanced usage</a>.</p>

<p><br /></p>
<blockquote>
  <p><strong>Xcode 10 Archive failed (i386 bitcode problem)</strong></p>
</blockquote>

<ol>
  <li>please use the device arch only framework <a href="/assets/framework/WoodPeckeriOS_device.framework.zip">WoodPeckeriOS_device.framework</a>, it‚Äôs full bitcode enabled. But I would suggest you use the full version above in most situations.</li>
</ol>

